				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				NPC, Vegalys Keldrane is upstairs in the north qeynos gate. he gives you the quest for your investigaters badge, after you prove you are &quot;serious&quot; by killing &quot;Guard Shilster&quot; ie Robbie Shilster. to find the guard goto the north karana wood bridge (which briges north and east karana), put your back to the wood bridge and face north karana, go right along the river, and you will find him. I am lvl 18 druid, he killed me the first time, because i did not know he was a caster. he hit me with a spell that read as follows, &quot;you writher in the grasp of agony, you have been hit for 171 non-melle dmg&quot; he also had fear, which i resisted, he resisted my grasping roots the first time i casted it but it took for a short time the next time i did. he did not hit very hard 2 bash 36 slash, but he killed me non the less that time. the second time i attacked him i used a grizzly bear to distract him i hit him with sting swarm and ignight and involk lighting i also grasping rooted him, i had my damage spells on, and he went down fairly quick. that time he was only able to get off a fear which i resisted and a life tap (i think) which read as follows &quot;your life begins to drain away&quot; which only dmg me 5pts and 11pts. when you kill him your faction get better with guards of qeynos and worse with kane bayle, circle of unseen hands and the bloodsabers. you get a rusty long sword, a qeynos guard kite shile and the corrupt qeynos guard helm plus exp. when you turn in the helm to V keldrane, your faction is better with qeynos guards, qeynos merchants and antonios bayle. worse with rune of scale and kane bayle. you get exp and the manual, which is used to complete the Investigators badge quest. I will follow info in the post above (investigators badge at this site) to continue the quest and post my further developments. 
